 or lower only.<br>When charm breaks if the animal was not kos to you to begin with it won't be kos after it breaks.<br><br>not to be confused with Call of Karana, the normal upgrade to our animal charm series.  Call follows the standard mob charm rules, 46 and under I think, and when charm breaks it hates your guts. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugadzoook.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Gadzoook</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/13/02 4:37:38 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2694.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tunare's Request</span><hr size=1> One thing to bear in mind is that (it used to, if it hasn't been fixed) the animal won't agro if the charm breaks naturally.  If you invis to loose booboo it will attack you same as if you'd used CoK or a similar spell.<br><br>-gadz <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umeowmia.showPublicProfile?language=EN>MeowMia</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/15/02 7:14:57 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2694.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tunare's Request</span><hr size=1> Argh, why do they make spells 55th level only usable on animals 35th level and below, they're all green :( <p><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=46280" target="_blank"><img src="http://www.belainimages.homestead.com/files/Leoparda_signature.JPG" border="0"></a>55th Druid</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#e6ebd7><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/usilicontraveller.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Silicon Traveller</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/15/02 10:02:29 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2694.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.freakygamers.com/smilies/s2/games/diablo/DRUIDD.GIF WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tunare's Request</span><hr size=1> you can charm any animal with call of karana (try charmin them big elephants in WW? - or the doggies in chardok?)<br><br>however, once charm breaks they get quite annoyed and you gotta deal with pet + mob ;)<br><br>glamour of tunare is probably a good idea beforehand, as it has no aggro component... and lowers resist (charm seems to stick better, and longer).<br><br>as to tunare's request.... sigh. semi fun only, coz you can charm greenies... (best you can find here i guess is griffons?)<br><br>overall, unless if you have dire charm... i wouldnt bother.<br>more trouble than its worth. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#f7f5e6><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utresjoli.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Tresjoli</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.shadow-striders.com/images/wolfIcon.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#333399>(2/20/02 10:39:04 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub13.ezboard.com/fthedruidsgrovespells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2694.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.cpinternet.com/~theduke/MythStuff/ez-tres.gif  WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Tunare's Request</span>